cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically object segmentation. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach to augment feedforward networks, which involves refining object segments using top-down information. This approach involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses accuracy improvements and optimization of the network architecture, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses the DeepMask network as a starting point, which suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
